---
// What You're Competing Against
---

<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-slate-50">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="section-line bg-red-500 mb-6"></div>
    <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-3xl md:text-4xl tracking-tight mb-3">
      What You're Competing Against
    </h2>
    <p class="font-body text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mb-10">
      The wealth gap isn't just an abstract number. It represents real economic power that directly affects your ability to compete.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
      <!-- Billionaires -->
      <div class="card p-6 border-t-4 border-blue-500">
        <div class="text-center mb-4">
          <div class="font-mono text-blue-600 text-sm font-semibold">905 BILLIONAIRES</div>
          <div class="stat-huge text-blue-600">$7.8T</div>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2">Combined wealth</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-center">
            <strong>905 people</strong> control more wealth than the bottom half of America combined.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Bottom 50% -->
      <div class="card p-6 border-t-4 border-red-500">
        <div class="text-center mb-4">
          <div class="font-mono text-red-600 text-sm font-semibold">66 MILLION HOUSEHOLDS</div>
          <div class="stat-huge text-red-600">$4.1T</div>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2">Combined wealth</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-center">
            <strong>66 million households</strong> — half of America — share less than billionaires alone.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Small Business Reality -->
    <div class="card p-6">
      <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4">
        The Small Business Reality
      </h3>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mb-6">
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">$69,119</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Average annual revenue</div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">$59,000</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Median owner salary</div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">78%</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Solo businesses under $50K</div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">50%</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Close within 5 years</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-xl text-center">
        <p class="font-body text-lg text-gray-700">
          At average small business revenue of $69K/year, it would take <strong class="text-red-600">124,638 years</strong> to match the average Forbes 400 billionaire's wealth.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <p class="font-mono text-sm text-gray-400 mt-4 text-center">
        Federal Reserve DFA Q2 2024 / SBA Office of Advocacy
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
